// =====================================================
// ui_import_product_material — bulk-CREATE product_material rows from an
// uploaded CSV file (3 columns: product_code, material_code, quantity).
//
// product_material fields:
//   fk_product_code          -> product.code
//   fk_material_details_code -> material_details.code
//   quantity
//
// SANDBOX NOTE (same environment as ui_import_material_code): SES lockdown
// blocks document.* property access, fetch(), writing to any global, and
// `new FileReader()`. So:
//   - Mounting follows ui_material_out's pattern: antd Modal.confirm() with
//     OK/Cancel hidden, custom buttons inside `content`, Modal.destroyAll()
//     to close.
//   - Files are read via Blob.prototype.text() on the File object antd's
//     Upload already hands us (an instance method on an existing object,
//     not a global we're instantiating — this one is allowed), parsed as
//     plain delimited text (comma/semicolon/tab, auto-detected).
//
// Stored as a `source_code` row named 'ui_import_product_material'.
// Loaded via loadCode(ctx, 'ui_import_product_material'); compiled with
// new Function('React','antd','dayjs','ctx', src)(React, antd, dayjs, ctx).
//
// EXPORTS (contract):
//   openModal({ ctx, onSaved })
//     — opens the wizard (pick file -> preview/validate -> confirm -> run ->
//       summary) via Modal.confirm. onSaved() fires once, after the modal is
//       closed, IF at least one row was actually created.
//
// Classification before running anything, per row { product_code,
// material_code, quantity_raw }:
//   - all three cells blank                          -> ignored entirely
//   - missing product_code and/or material_code       -> skipped, invalid
//   - quantity blank (codes present)                  -> row is still
//     created, `quantity` is simply left unset (not sent as 0 or null)
//   - quantity present but not a valid number         -> skipped, invalid
//   - product_code not found in product                -> skipped, listed
//   - material_code not found in material_details       -> skipped, listed
//   - (product_code, material_code) pair already exists
//     in product_material                              -> skipped as duplicate
//   - otherwise                                        -> created
//
// NOTE (2026-07): lookup queries (products/materials/existing pairs) converted
// from raw ctx.sql to ctx.api.resource().list() — ctx.sql.save() is admin/root-
// gated and silently fails for non-admin roles (see README §3). These lookups
// pull whole tables with no WHERE clause, so a paginating fetchAllRows helper
// was added to avoid silently truncating results past one page — a single
// .list() call alone would cap at pageSize and could miss codes/pairs on
// larger tables, breaking duplicate/existence detection. Do not revert to raw
// SQL or drop the pagination loop.
